HEADWORD: Monazite
<hw>Mon"a*zite</hw> <pr>(m⟦ocr⟧n"⟦adot⟧*z⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[From Gr. <grk>mona`zein</grk> to be solitary, in allusion to its
isolated crystals.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring
usually in small isolated crystals, -- a phosphate of the cerium
metals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

